comment.shortText:
If using the new style context, re-declare this in your class to be the
`React.ContextType` of your `static contextType`.
Should be used with type annotation or static contextType.
comment.text:
```ts
static contextType = MyContext
// For TS pre-3.7:
context!: React.ContextType<typeof MyContext>
// For TS 3.7 and above:
declare context: React.ContextType<typeof MyContext>
```

comment.shortText: If set, `this.context` will be set at runtime to the current value of the given Context.

Runs before React applies the result of `render` to the document, and
returns an object to be given to componentDidUpdate. Useful for saving
things such as scroll position before `render` causes changes to it.

Note: the presence of getSnapshotBeforeUpdate prevents any of the deprecated
lifecycle events from running.

comment.shortText: Called to determine whether the change in props and state should trigger a re-render.
comment.text:
`Component` always returns true.
`PureComponent` implements a shallow comparison on props and state and returns true if any
props or states have changed.

If false is returned, `Component#render`, `componentWillUpdate`
and `componentDidUpdate` will not be called.

Function used to determine the order of the elements. It is expected to return

```

Interface for items that provide a React node label (anything that React can render). Implementing this can save you having to pass
explicit functions to label an item in other parts of the system (eg. for [AsyncChoices](doc:AsyncChoices))
comment.text: See [isNodeLabeled](doc:isNodeLabeled) and [getNodeLabel](doc:getNodeLabel).

comment.shortText: Return the node label for this item. This can be anything renderable by React.
comment.text:
See [isNodeLabeled](doc:isNodeLabeled) to test for support and [getNodeLabel](doc:getNodeLabel) for easiest way
to get the label.

comment.shortText:
Interface for items that provide a plain text label. Implementing this can save you having to pass
explicit functions to label an item in other parts of the system (eg. for [AsyncChoices](doc:AsyncChoices))
comment.text: See [isTextLabeled](doc:isTextLabeled) and [getTextLabel](doc:getTextLabel).

comment.shortText: Return the plain text label for this item. This must return a string
comment.text:
See [isTextLabeled](doc:isTextLabeled) to test for support and [getTextLabel](doc:getTextLabel) for easiest way
to get the label.

comment.shortText: Get a React node label from an item
comment.text:
If item implements `getNodeLabel` that will be used otherwise `getLabel` will be used.

If neither are defined an error is thrown. To conditional call this check if labeled first
with `isLabeled`.

comment.shortText: Get a plain text label from an item
comment.text:
If does not implement TextLabeled an error is thrown. To conditional call this check if labeled first
with `isTextLabeled`.

Check if a value conforms to NodeLabeled
Check if a value conforms to TextLabeled

comment.text:
`Component` always returns true.
`PureComponent` implements a shallow comparison on props and state and returns true if any
props or states have changed.

If false is returned, `Component#render`, `componentWillUpdate`
and `componentDidUpdate` will not be called.

Interface for items that provide a React node label (anything that React can render). Implementing this can save you having to pass
explicit functions to label an item in other parts of the system (eg. for [AsyncChoices](doc:AsyncChoices))
comment.text: See [isNodeLabeled](doc:isNodeLabeled) and [getNodeLabel](doc:getNodeLabel).

comment.shortText: Return the node label for this item. This can be anything renderable by React.
comment.text:
See [isNodeLabeled](doc:isNodeLabeled) to test for support and [getNodeLabel](doc:getNodeLabel) for easiest way
to get the label.

comment.shortText:
Interface for items that provide a plain text label. Implementing this can save you having to pass
explicit functions to label an item in other parts of the system (eg. for [AsyncChoices](doc:AsyncChoices))
comment.text: See [isTextLabeled](doc:isTextLabeled) and [getTextLabel](doc:getTextLabel).

comment.shortText: Return the plain text label for this item. This must return a string
comment.text:
See [isTextLabeled](doc:isTextLabeled) to test for support and [getTextLabel](doc:getTextLabel) for easiest way
to get the label.

comment.shortText: Get a React node label from an item
comment.text:
If item implements `getNodeLabel` that will be used otherwise `getLabel` will be used.

If neither are defined an error is thrown. To conditional call this check if labeled first
with `isLabeled`.

comment.shortText: Get a plain text label from an item
comment.text:
If does not implement TextLabeled an error is thrown. To conditional call this check if labeled first
with `isTextLabeled`.

comment.shortText: Check if item supports either text or React node labels
Check if a value conforms to NodeLabeled
Check if a value conforms to TextLabeled
